name: Wrike
description: Add a Wrike Instance to connect your existing Wrike account to the Help Desk Hub, allowing you to manage your incidents, priorities, statuses, users, etc. across multiple Help Desk Elements. You will need your Wrike account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. Allowed searches are plainText (boolean), and updatedDate (start and end). For example, to search for comments posted between a date range (max range of seven days), the search expression will be where=updatedDate='{"start": "2016-05-10T15:27:37Z","end": "2016-05-17T15:27:37Z"}'.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. Allowed searches are me (boolean, if 'true' returns only timelogs from current user), plainText (boolean),  subTasks (boolean), descendants (boolean), trackedDate (start and end), and createdDate (start and end). For example, to search for comments posted between a date range (max range of seven days), the search expression will be where=createdDate='{"start": "2016-05-10T15:27:37Z","end": "2016-05-17T15:27:37Z"}'.
